# Psychiatric Emergencies

Practical educational notes on psychiatric emergencies, aimed at clinicians, residents, and students.

## Purpose
- Provide a structured overview of common psychiatric emergencies
- Support initial assessment and clinical reasoning
- Offer concise, practical educational content

## Planned subtopics
- Suicide risk assessment and management
- Acute agitation and behavioral emergencies
- Severe anxiety and panic crises
- Acute psychotic episodes
- Substance-related emergencies
- Initial management and referral pathways

> Note: Content in this repository is for educational purposes only and does not replace formal clinical training, local protocols, or individualized medical care.
